The new issue of <a href="http://www.springerlink.com/content/v6167602g164/?p=071f38dabe04459e8f12387817174cd3&pi=0">Evolution: Education and Outreach is now online</a>.  It is, of course, a 'Darwin' issue.  It includes <a href="http://pandasthumb.org/archives/2009/02/majerus-tribute.html">the late Michael Majerus'</a> final word on the pedagogical utility of <i>Biston betularia</i>, the peppered moth.  The papers are linked below the fold.  Links are to HTML versions; pdf versions are also available at the main site linked above.


